# CODEOWNERS — auto-review routing for PRs
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Pattern matching: last matching pattern wins.
# Each line: <pattern> <@owner1> <@owner2> ...

# ── 1. Default owner (fallback for any file not matched below) ──────────────
# Catch-all ensures every PR gets at least one reviewer auto-requested.
*                                   @OpenSIN-Code/sin-code-maintainers

# ── 2. Core backend — strict review (2 owners required) ────────────────────
# lib/sin/ and app/api/ are the sin-code integration layer;
# bugs here break the entire chat → backend pipeline.
/lib/sin/                           @Delqhi
/app/api/                           @Delqhi

# ── 3. CI/CD & infrastructure — strict review ──────────────────────────────
# Workflow, Docker, and reverse-proxy changes can silently break
# deploys or introduce supply-chain risk.
/.github/workflows/                 @Delqhi
/Dockerfile*                        @Delqhi
/docker-compose.yml                 @Delqhi
/Caddyfile                          @Delqhi

# ── 4. Frontend — normal review ────────────────────────────────────────────
# UI components and page routes; lower blast radius than backend.
/app/                               @OpenSIN-Code/sin-code-maintainers
/components/                        @OpenSIN-Code/sin-code-maintainers

# ── 5. Docs — light review ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Markdown and docs carry no runtime risk.
/*.md                               @OpenSIN-Code/sin-code-maintainers
/docs/                              @OpenSIN-Code/sin-code-maintainers

# ── 6. Secrets-sensitive — strict review ────────────────────────────────────
# .env files and secrets directory must never leak real values.
/.env*                              @Delqhi
/secrets/                            @Delqhi
